   449      5889    3571127.0    606.4     15.1              Hi =  np.linalg.inv(H.T @ H)
   450      5889     190018.0     32.3      0.8              Hi2=cls.Hidict[keyval]
   451      5889     596130.0    101.2      2.5              u_vec = (H @ Hi)[0:,0]
   452                                                   else:
   453                                                       # Main estimator
   454                                                       Hi =  np.linalg.inv(H.T @ H)
   455                                                       u_vec = (H @ Hi)[0:,0]
   456                                                       Hi2 = np.eye(Ns) - np.linalg.multi_dot([H,Hi,H.T])
   457                                                       cls.Hidict[keyval] = Hi2
   458                                           
   459                                                   # Main estimator
   460                                                   # rd fitting
   461      5889     486204.0     82.6      2.1          v_hat = -Me @ u_vec # v_x estimate
   462      5889    2813270.0    477.7     11.9          M1var = (np.sum( CRB * np.array([cls.d**2, cls.r**2]).T,1) 
   463      5889    1288371.0    218.8      5.5          + np.prod(CRB,1) )
   464                                                   # Fitting Error compuation (For each target)
   465      5889     438606.0     74.5      1.9          FA1 = Me @ Hi2
   466                                                   
   467                                                   # r2 fitting
   468      5889     343484.0     58.3      1.5          Me2_centered = (Me2 - ( L**2 ))
   469      5889     479205.0     81.4      2.0          x_hat = -Me2_centered @ u_vec/2
   470      5889    1095582.0    186.0      4.6          M2var = (4*CRB[:,0] * np.array( cls.r**2) + CRB[:,0]**2)# Ignoring higher order terms
   471                                                   # Fitting Error compuation (For each target)
   472      5889     317881.0     54.0      1.3          FA2 = Me2_centered @ Hi2
   473                                                   # Get constants
   474                                                   # Z = cls.Zdict[Ns-2]
   475                                                   # Wi = cls.Widict[Ns-2]
   476                                                   
   477                                                   # N_mat = Me @ Z.T + (v_hat *L) @(Z.T) # eta
   478                                                   # V_mat = N_mat @ Wi  # Optimal dual var.
   479                                                   # g_nu = np.sqrt(np.sum(N_mat * V_mat) - np.sum((V_mat@Z)**2)/4)
   480                                                   
   481                                                   # N_mat2 = Me2 @ Z.T + 2*x_hat *L @ (Z.T) - ( L*L ) @ Z.T # eta
   482                                                   # U_mat = N_mat2 @ Wi # Optimal dual var.
   483                                                   # g_nu2 = np.sqrt(np.sum(N_mat2 * U_mat) - np.sum((U_mat@Z)**2)/4)
   484                                                   # cls.gc = ((cfg.rd_wt[0]*(V_mat@Z/2)**2/M1var + cfg.rd_wt[1]*((U_mat@Z/2)**2)/M2var))
   485      5889     924713.0    157.0      3.9          cls.gc = ((cfg.rd_wt[0]*(FA1**2)/M1var + cfg.rd_wt[1]*((FA2)**2)/M2var))
   486                                                   
   487      5889     459942.0     78.1      2.0          xsa = x_hat - L
   488      5889    2988436.0    507.5     12.7          y_est = np.sqrt(abs(np.mean(Me2 - xsa **2))) # TODO: handle negative value properly
   489      5889    2309420.0    392.2      9.8          vy_est = np.mean(Me - v_hat*xsa) / y_est # Estimated using other estimates
   490                                                   
   491      5889     413733.0     70.3      1.8          Stn = np.array([x_hat, y_est, v_hat, vy_est])
   492                                                   # Pn = np.diag([g_nu, g_nu2])
   493      5889    1448047.0    245.9      6.1          Pn = np.diag([1, 1, 1, 1])
   494      5889     317296.0     53.9      1.3          new_state = State(Stn, Pn)
   495      5889     108404.0     18.4      0.5          return new_state
